Program: The History Hour
Title: The Fake IDs That Saved Jewish Lives
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0wd
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 29 Oct 2017
How tens of thousands of Hungarian Jews escaped the Nazis by using false papers; what happened when abortion became illegal overnight in 1960s Romania; the murder of campaigning Nigerian journalist Dele Giwa; the creation of British satire magazine Private Eye; and the love affair between writers Jean-Paul Sartre and Simone de Beauvoir. Photo: False Hungarian ID document (BBC) Show less